cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to infer the polarity of relationships between people in narrative summaries. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses structured prediction models, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of clustering-based approaches suggests the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval and semantic features, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of social community structure suggests the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
